<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>42-1002</num>
  <heading>General power.</heading>
  <text>A power is general where it authorizes the alienation in fee, by means of a conveyance, will, or charge, of the lands embraced in the power to any alienee whatever.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="§1038">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1353, ch. 854, § 1038</annotation>
